x4freetext: A multilayered C/LIF/Au sample was used for the cross
section measurements. A thin lif film (about 50
mug/cm2) was evaporated on a self-supporting C target
(about 30 mug/cm2) and further coated with a thin Au
layer (about 20 mug/cm2) for beam dose normalization;
the gold layer could also prevent lithium fluoride from
being oxidised.
A silicon surface barrier detector of 50 mm2
area, 500 mumeters thickness and 12 KeV FWHM energy
resolution.

x4codes.hlp: Universidad Autonoma de Madrid, Madrid, Spain

x4freetext: The HVEE 5 MV Tandetron accelerator
See sample.
During the measurements proton beam currents
were in the range 10-40-Na, depending on beam energy,
in order to keep the count rate low enough to have
negligible pile-up effects (<0.5%).  Each measurement
was allowed to continue until obtaining at least 2000
counts in all the elastic scattering peaks.

x4freetext: The contributions to the error in the
cross-section value from area density ratio.
The  conservative estimate is obtained for the
uncertainties of the absolute cross-sections , at all
the beam energies by adding "non-statistical"
contributions linearly to the statistical errors from
the peak areas.
